Who Am I

Past

Present

Future

Talha was an early bloomer in the world of coding, tinkering with code since his pre-high school days, fueled by an insatiable curiosity and self-guided learning approach. He dissected games and delved into source codes, keeping draft copies to ponder over the intricate logic behind them.

​

During his intermediate college years, Talha seamlessly transitioned into the professional realm, By the time he graduated with his bachelor's degree, he had already amassed years of invaluable professional experience.

Talha's journey continued as he ventured into diverse domains, from large-scale fabric export with JK Group to streamlining operations in the graphics industry with Bricklay. He then embarked on an exhilarating startup experience with Lighthouse within real-estate industiry, where he single-handedly nurtured a fledgling web app into a multi-million dollar venture, showcasing his ability to thrive in dynamic environments. 

​

His career trajectory soared as he joined Hotel Engine, a top-tier Fortune 300 company, as a Lead Engineer, Now, as the Director of Engineering at Dirayaah, Talha channels his boundless passion and eagerness to innovate into crafting interactive web game platforms for learning, embodying his relentless pursuit of excellence.

Talha envisions himself as a trailblazer in the tech industry, spearheading groundbreaking innovations and ushering in a new era of creative and transformative technologies. He thrives on challenging himself by exploring the intricacies of programming, algorithms, and game dynamics, constantly pushing the boundaries of his skills and knowledge to stay ahead of the curve.
